                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Dudley</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-06-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegram June 1. Brazilian minister for foreign affairs will instruct
                    Brazilian representative at Quito and Lima to present note <pb facs="0579"
                        n="467" xml:id="pg_467"/> identical with your aide-mémoire to the
                    representatives of Ecuador and Peru, and authorizes me to assure you he will
                    endeavor to promote desired Chilean cooperation at Quito.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dudley.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
